      <hr /><a name="skip_menu"></a><h1><span>382</span> - <span>Medium of Performance</span><span> (R)</span></h1>
      <hr />
      <div class="formatname">MARC 21 Authority - full</div>
      <div class="datename">April 2015</div>
      <hr />
      <table width="100%" class="indicators">
         <tr>
            <th width="45%"> First Indicator </th>
            <th width="45%"> Second Indicator </th>
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td><em>Display constant controller</em><br /><span># - No information provided</span><br /><span>0 - Medium of performance</span><br /><span>1 - Partial medium of performance</span><br /><br /></td>
            <td><em>Undefined</em><br /><span># - Undefined</span><br /><br /></td>
         </tr>
      </table>
      <hr />
      <table width="100%" class="subfields">
         <tr>
            <td width="50%"></td>
            <td width="50%"></td>
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <th colspan="2">Subfield Codes</th>
         </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>
               <ul class="nomark">
                  <li>$a - Medium of performance<span> (R)</span></li>
                  <li>$b - Soloist<span> (R)</span></li>
                  <li>$d - Doubling instrument<span> (R)</span></li>
                  <li>$e - Number of ensembles<span> (R)</span></li>
                  <li>$n - Number of performers of the same medium<span> (R)</span></li>
                  <li>$p - Alternative medium of performance<span> (R)</span></li>
               </ul>
            </td>
            <td>
               <ul class="nomark">
                  <li>$s - Total number of performers<span> (NR)</span></li>
                  <li>$v - Note<span> (R)</span></li>
                  <li>$0 - Authority record control number or standard number<span> (R)</span></li>
                  <li>$2 - Source of term<span> (NR)</span></li>
                  <li>$6 - Linkage<span> (NR)</span></li>
                  <li>$8 - Field link and sequence number<span> (R)</span></li>
               </ul>
            </td>
         </tr>
      </table>
      <hr />
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <div class="definition">
         <div>
            <p>The instrumental, vocal, and/or other medium of performance for which a musical
               				work was originally conceived or for which a musical expression is written or
               performed.  
               				May be used to differentiate a musical work or expression from another with the
               same title.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div>
            <p>Multiple mediums from the same source vocabulary may be recorded in the 
				same field in separate occurrences of subfields $a (Medium of 
				performance), $b (Soloist), $d (Doubling instrument), or $p 
			  (Alternative medium of performance).  Multiple mediums from the same source vocabulary may
				also be recorded in separate occurrences of the field if each medium is controlled by an Authority
				record control number or standard number in subfield $0.  Terms from different 
			  source vocabularies are recorded in separate
				occurrences of the field.</p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <div class="guidelines">
         <div>
            <p></p>
         </div>
         <h4><span class="box">â </span> INDICATORS
         </h4>
         <div class="indicators">
            <div class="indicator">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>First Indicator - Display constant controller</strong></p>
                  <div>
                     <p></p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="value">
                     <div><span class="valueLabel"># - No information provided</span><div>
                           <p></p>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="value">
                     <div><span class="valueLabel">0 - Medium of performance</span><div>
                           <p>The complete medium of performance of the musical work/expression.</p>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="value">
                     <div><span class="valueLabel">1 - Partial medium of performance</span><div>
                           <p>Incomplete medium of performance of the musical work/expression. To be
                              		          used when certain instruments or voices are prominent but the complete
                              
                              		          instrumentation is unknown to the cataloger.
                           </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="example">
                           <table>
                              <tr>
                                 <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                                 <td colspan="9"><strong>11</strong><strong>$a</strong>didjeridu<strong>$n</strong>1<em><span><br /><span>[A sound recording of didjeridu music, in which the 
                                             		            didjeridu is prominent, but other instruments are not identified.]</span></span></em></td>
                              </tr>
                           </table>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicator">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>Second Indicator - Undefined</strong></p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Undefined and contains a blank (#).</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <h4><span class="box">â </span> SUBFIELD CODES
         </h4>
         <div class="subfields">
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$a - Medium of performance</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>A term that indicates the instrumental, vocal, and/or other medium of performance.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td>100</td>
                           <td colspan="9">1#$aMahler, Gustav,$d1860-1911.$tSymphonies,$nno. 2,$rC minor</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>soprano<strong>$a</strong>alto<strong>$a</strong>mixed voices<strong>$a</strong>orchestra
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td>384</td>
                           <td colspan="9">##$aC minor</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td>383</td>
                           <td colspan="9">##$ano. 2</td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td>100</td>
                           <td colspan="9">1#$aFaith, Richard,$d1926-$tMiniatures</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>oboe<strong>$a</strong>piano
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>clarinet<strong>$a</strong>piano<em><span><br /><span>[In this example there are different parts for performance purposes.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td>100</td>
                           <td colspan="9">1#$aBeethoven, Ludwig van,$d1770-1827.$tSonatas,$mpiano,$nno. 14, op. 27, no. 2,$rC# minor</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>piano
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td>383</td>
                           <td colspan="9">##$ano. 14,$bop. 27, no. 2</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td>384</td>
                           <td colspan="9">##$aC# minor</td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$b - Soloist</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Medium of performance term for a soloist (a featured instrument or voice accompanied
                        by an ensemble).
                     </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>0#</strong><strong>$b</strong>flute<strong>$a</strong>orchestra<em><span><br /><span>[A work for flute accompanied by orchestra.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$d - Doubling instrument</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Medium of performance term for the instrument(s)/voice(s) a performer in a musical work/expression
		        plays in addition to the primary instrument/voice. Multiple doubling instruments may be recorded in
		        separate occurrences of subfield $d. They may also be recorded in separate occurrences of the field
		        if each medium is controlled by an Authority record control number or standard number in subfield $0.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>0#</strong><strong>$a</strong>flute<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$d</strong>piccolo<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$d</strong>alto flute<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$d</strong>bass flute<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$s</strong>1<em><span><br /><span>[A work for solo flute, doubling piccolo, doubling alto flute, and doubling bass flute.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$e - Number of ensembles</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Number of ensembles named in the preceding subfield. Use after $a (Medium of performance)
						or $p (Alternative medium of performance).</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>01</strong><strong>$b</strong>harpsichord<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$b</strong>piano<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$a</strong>chamber orchestra<strong>$e</strong>2<strong>$2</strong>lcmpt<em><span><br /><span>[A double concerto for harpsichord and piano with two chamber orchestras.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>01</strong><strong>$a</strong>violin<strong>$n</strong>2<strong>$a</strong>soprano voice<strong>$n</strong>2<strong>$a</strong>alto voice<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$a</strong>tenor voice<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$a</strong>bass voice<strong>$n</strong>2<strong>$a</strong>mixed chorus<strong>$e</strong>2<strong>$a</strong>continuo<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$2</strong>lcmpt<em><span><br /><span>[A work for two violins, individual SSATBB voices, two mixed choirs, and continuo.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$n - Number of performers of the same medium</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Number of performers of the medium named in the preceding subfield.  Use after 
		        subfield $a (Medium of performance), $b (Soloist), $d (Doubling
		        instrument), or $p (Alternative medium of performance). Subfield $n may
		        be omitted if the number equals 1.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>0#</strong><strong>$a</strong>trumpet<strong>$n</strong>2<strong>$a</strong>trombone<strong>$n</strong>2<strong>$s</strong>4<em><span><br /><span>[A work for two trumpets and two trombones.]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$p - Alternative medium of performance</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Medium of performance term for an alternative instrument, vocal, and/or other medium of performance, given
		        as an alternative to its primary medium of performance in preceding subfield $a, $b, or $d.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>0#</strong><strong>$p</strong>clarinet<strong>$v</strong>alternative for violin<strong>$2</strong>gnd
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$s - Total number of performers</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Total number of performers needed to perform in the musical work/expression.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>0#</strong><strong>$a</strong>soprano<strong>$n</strong>2<strong>$a</strong>mezzo-soprano<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$a</strong>tenor saxophone<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$d</strong>bass clarinet<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$a</strong>trumpet<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$a</strong>piano<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$a</strong>violin<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$d</strong>viola<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$a</strong>double bass<strong>$n</strong>1<strong>$s</strong>8<em><span><br /><span>[A work for 2 sopranos, one mezzo-soprano, tenor saxophone
                                       		          (doubling bass clarinet), C trumpet, piano, violin (doubling viola), and
                                       		          double bass--8 total performers).]</span></span></em></td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$v - Note</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Note for information that is not kept otherwise in the subfields of the field.  May
                        contain a description 
                        		        of the relationship between an alternative medium of performance and its
                        primary medium of performance, or other
                        		        textual information.
                     </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="example">
                     <table>
                        <tr>
                           <td><strong>382</strong></td>
                           <td colspan="9"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>didjeridu<strong>$v</strong>didjeridu is prominent, but other instruments are not identified<strong>$2</strong>gnd
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$0 - Authority record control number or standard number</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$2 - Source of term</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>MARC code that identifies the source of the term in subfield $a when it is from a
						controlled list.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                     <p>Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/standards/sourcelist/musical-instrumentation.html">Musical Instrumentation
                              						and Voice Code Source Codes</a></em>.
                        					
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>CONTENT DESIGNATOR HISTORY</h3>
      <div class="history">
         <div class="indicatorHistory"><em>Indicator 1 - Type of edition [NEW, 2012]</em><div class="valuehistory">
               <div><em># - No information provided [NEW, 2012]</em></div>
            </div>
            <div>
               <p></p>
            </div>
            <div class="valuehistory">
               <div><em>0 - Medium of performance [NEW, 2012]</em></div>
            </div>
            <div>
               <p></p>
            </div>
            <div class="valuehistory">
               <div><em>1 - Partial medium of performance [NEW, 2012]</em></div>
            </div>
            <div>
               <p>Prior to 2012 Indicator 1 was undefined</p>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$b - Soloist [NEW, 2012]</em></div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$d - Doubling instrument [NEW, 2012]</em></div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$e - Number of ensembles [NEW, 2015]</em></div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$p - Alternative medium of performance [NEW, 2012]</em></div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$n - Number of performers of the same medium [NEW, 2012]</em></div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$s - Total number of performers [NEW, 2012]</em></div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$s - Total number of performers [CHANGED, 2014]</em><div class="subfieldHistoryDsc">
                  <p>Repeatability corrected</p>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$v - Note [NEW, 2012]</em></div>
         </div>
      </div>
